         <abstract id="aspace_45ffa41b826b0c97bd4651608a0f8a5b">The Duke Memorial was formed in 1929
            to honor Washington, Benjamin N., and James B. Duke. The group worked on several
            projects, including building the Memorial Chapel in Duke Chapel, financing the purchase
            of Duke Homestead, and building a statue of James B. Duke. The collection consists
            mainly of financial documents, as well as general correspondence, minutes, and proposals
            and suggestions. Major topics include the construction of Memorial Chapel and the
            sarcophagi within, the purchase of Duke Homestead, and the financing of the James B.
            Duke Statue. Major correspondents include James A. Thomas, W. W. Flowers, and Alex H.
            Sands. English.</abstract>
